sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K324003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part combines two biobricks, a TetR repressible promoter+RBS (BBa_J13002) and the LacI regulatory protein in RFC25 assembly (BBa_K324000). This BioBrick allows the expression of LacI when inserted into E. coli, for the purpose of testing constructs controlled by the LacI promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julius Ho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
A simple Biobrick assembly was conducted to join the TetR promoter+RBS (BBa_J13002) with LacI (BBa_K324000). J13002 was obtained from the 2010 Spring Distribution, while K324000 was adapted by 2010 Brown iGEM from an existing part. See the part's page for further details
http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_J13002 http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_K324000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: These parts were joined together with standard biobrick assembly, even though the LacI protein was in RFC25 and thus capable of protein fusion assembly as well.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K324000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: LacI repressor protein in RFC25 format
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of the lacI repressor protein (BBa_I732100) optimized with endings for protein fusion in the Freiburg assembly format (RFC25). There is also a 6-his tag appended to the C-terminus for easy purification using Ni-affinity column. RFC 25 prefix/suffix and 6-his sequences attached via PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Julius Ho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: http://partsregistry.org/Part:BBa_I732100 Submitted by the USTC '07 iGEM team, taken from the 2010 Spring Distribution
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 6-his tag was appended to the 3' end of this protein to allow for purification upon expression in E. coli. We chose a C-terminal tag to avoid isolation of incompletely translated peptides.
